"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984850","Attorney General","false","2018-10-16","<p>Details of Ministers’ overseas travel are published quarterly and are available on GOV.UK.</p><p>No Officials from the Attorney General’s Office have visited the Irish Border in the past 12 months.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-10-16T11:57:38.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984850/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984850/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984850/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-10-10","Attorney General: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many and which (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have visited the Irish border in the last 12 months; when those visits took place; and how long they spent at the border in each of those visits.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","177799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984851","Cabinet Office","false","2018-10-18","<p>a) Ministers have travelled between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland. Details of Ministers’ overseas travel are published quarterly and are available on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p><p>b) Details of business expenses incurred by senior officials include domestic and international travel. This information is also published quarterly and is available on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested for all officials in my Department is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-10-18T12:46:11.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984851/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984851/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984851/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-10","Cabinet Office: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many and which (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have visited the Irish border in the last 12 months; when those visits took place; and how long they spent at the border in each of those visits.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","177800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984852","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-10-18","<p>Ministers and officials from the Department at all levels have visited both Northern Ireland and Ireland regularly to gain understanding of the issues relating to the border. My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has visited Belfast in both May and August this year, accompanied by my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland. My rt. hon Friend the Minister of State for Energy and Clean Growth met the Irish Minister for Business in London in June, and my hon. Friend the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State, Minister for Business and Industry visited Dublin in December last year.</p><p>Officials working on Energy Networks and on Customs visit regularly, holding extensive meetings with local officials and businesses to understand in detail the relevant areas of concern, including the Single Electricity Market and cross-border trade. BEIS has built a clear picture of cross-border supply chains of a number of businesses (including SMEs) and East-West and North-South trade flows.</p><p>In addition, Northern Ireland Office Ministers have also conducted an extensive programme of engagement in Northern Ireland on EU exit with a wide range of stakeholders.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-10-18T15:01:30.853Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984852/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984852/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984852/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-10","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many and which (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have visited the Irish border in the last 12 months; when those visits took place; and how long they spent at the border in each of those visits.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","177801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984853","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-10-19","<p>a) No such trips have taken place. Details of Ministers’ overseas travel are published quarterly and are available on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p><p>b) Details of business expenses incurred by senior officials include domestic and international travel. This information is also published quarterly and is available on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested for all officials in my Department is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-10-19T10:53:41.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984853/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984853/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984853/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-10-10","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many and which (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have visited the Irish border in the last 12 months; when those visits took place; and how long they spent at the border in each of those visits.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","177802"
