"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984870","Home Office","false","2018-10-18","<p>Dame Judith Hackitt’s report on Building Regulations and Fire Safety calls for major reform of the regulatory system and for culture change across the construction industry and fire safety sector.</p><p>The government agreed with the broad principles of the report and committed to bring forward legislation. The Home Office and the Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government are working with partners to consider the detail of Dame Judith’s recommendations and the government will make a statement on implementation of the reforms later in the autumn.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-10-18T16:34:18.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984870/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984870/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-10","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make an assessment of the effect of the Grenfell Tower fire on the adequacy of the provisions on residential buildings in the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","177601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984871","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-10-15","<p>Under successive governments the Department has never kept records on numbers contacting the Department or pension providers on having been unaware that they had a pension which had been contracted out.</p><p> </p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-10-15T16:50:29.74Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984871/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984871/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984871/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-10","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have contacted (a) her Department and (b) pension providers on having been unaware that they had a pension which had been contracted out.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","177819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984872","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-10-15","<p>Universal Credit Claimants are able to reset their password online unless they have forgotten all of their details.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently making some improvements which we hope will simplify the process for claimants.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-10-15T16:46:43.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984872/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984872/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984872/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-10","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the oral contribution of 7 February 2018, Official Report, column 1489, when an online password reset function will be implemented for universal credit claimants.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","177820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984873","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>Reserve infantry soldiers will need to meet the new In-Service Physical Employment Standards to be eligible for the Certificate of Efficiency from April 2019. Due to the nature of the Reserve commitment (e.g. time limitations) they will take a practical alternative version of the new Army Role Fitness Test (RFT). This has been developed to predict success at the RFT and is not a lower standard. Army Reserve personnel deploying on operations or attending specific training courses (which are yet to be defined), will take the full RFT.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-10-15T16:55:07.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984873/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984873/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984873/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-10","Army Reserve: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether reserve infantry soldiers will have to pass the Army's new In-Service Physical Employment Standards when it comes into effect as part of mandatory training obligations in order to be eligible for award of the Certificate of Efficiency and therefore training bounty.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","177628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984874","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-10-17","<p>The British Government monitors events in Bahrain closely. Where we have concerns on specific issues, including prison conditions, we raise these with the Bahraini authorities. We encourage those with concerns about treatment in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-10-17T16:14:41.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984874/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984874/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984874/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-10","Bahrain: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the prison conditions experienced in Bahrain.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","177777"
